<li id="cite_note-38"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In depictions since the 12th century, according to Schiller p.&#160;56. Specifically the man who <a href="Saint_Peter" title="Saint Peter">Saint Peter</a> attacks with a sword often had the lantern, which he drops to the ground when attacked. The scenes of the <i><a href="Agony_in_the_Garden" title="Agony in the Garden">Agony in the Garden</a></i> of Gethsemane and the <i>Arrest of Christ</i> were central in the development of the depiction of nocturnal scenes in art.</span></li>
